race.comment: Looks a good race for DURHAM LEGACY (3) who returned from a break with a fourth at Benalla when trying to lead throughout but was nabbed late. Fitter and in this easier company will take catching. ECHUCA MOAMA (5) has shown some ability last campaign and returns for a new yard. Fitter for a trial and has placed fresh. Should hit the ground running. WYMAN LAKE (9) raced on pace but weakened late on slow ground last time. Firmer footing will help and has the blinkers added. Worth another chance. RENEGE (1) led and was run over late last time over the border. Has placed 6/12 and looks a genuine hope off the inside draw. MANHATTAN DARLING (8) was in the market on debut earlier in the year but was well beaten. Returns from a long break without a jump-out or trial and has the claimer aboard. Watch the betting.
